    server_name yourdomain.com;

    # Redirect all HTTP traffic to HTTPS
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}
```

Replace `/path/to/your_certificate.crt` and `/path/to/your_certificate.key` with the actual paths to your `.crt` and `.key` files. Update `yourdomain.com`, `backend_server_ip`, and `backend_port` with your actual domain and backend service information.

After saving the configuration file (usually located in `/etc/nginx/sites-available/`), test the configuration with `sudo nginx -t`. If the test is successful, reload Nginx with `sudo systemctl reload nginx`.

